sharing this model info using netron - 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/31642462/155502598-c6b72129-eae5-4509-aa11-47fdcc01d09a.png)

`The input tensor cannot be reshaped to the requested shape. Input shape:{1,25}, requested shape:{50}`

The total size of the tensor should match the new shape. In this case the input has size of 25, it can not become 50.

> `The input tensor cannot be reshaped to the requested shape. Input shape:{1,25}, requested shape:{50}`
> 
> The total size of the tensor should match the new shape. In this case the input has size of 25, it can not become 50.

But onnx model has dynamic axis. Why this cannot reshaped?
This is models dimensions-
Graph Input] name: input, shape: [0, 0] [Graph Input] name: input_lengths, shape: [0] [Graph Output] name: output, shape: [0, 0, 0]
looking forward to hear from community

This issue is basically - while exportin torch model to onnx, we have specified dummy_input and that dummy_input shape is somehow taken as fixed parameter to onnx model. Thats why it hold that dummy_shape as fixed and cannot taken dynamic input shape.
And, if I check onnx model inputs shape - it is expected.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/31642462/157592650-fe5bc97c-ca42-4e38-8493-f931e2251b67.png)

Model Output graph -

This is the code-
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/31642462/157602617-9da43f59-23eb-4fad-ae22-0e3de50769dc.png)

@spandantiwari 
@TomWildenhain-Microsoft
@hariharans29
@houseroad @lara-hdr @BowenBao @neginraoof
